pageType: content
background:
  type: solid
  color: "$background"
elements:
  - elementId: top-bar
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [0, 0, 1280, 6]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"
  - elementId: title
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 18, 1100, 38]
    content:
      style: "$actionTitle"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Search Achieves 10.3x ROAS at H30 But Loses 4.5x When Budget Doubles</p>
  - elementId: divider
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [60, 58, 1160, 1]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$border"
  - elementId: left-big-number
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 72, 350, 130]
    content:
      align: [left, top]
      lineHeight: 1.2
      text: |
        <p><span style="font-size:64px; color:$primary; font-family:Oranienbaum;">10.33x</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-size:16px; color:$secondary;">H30 Baseline ROAS</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-size:14px; color:$secondary;">Daily Spend: $463</span></p>
  - elementId: left-horizons
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 212, 350, 100]
    content:
      fontSize: 16
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>H30:</strong> 10.33x baseline</p>
        <p><strong>H60:</strong> 5.43x baseline</p>
        <p><strong>H90:</strong> 3.12x baseline</p>
  - elementId: search-chart
    elementType: chart
    bounds: [440, 72, 780, 240]
    type: bar
    data:
      - {horizon: "H30", baseline: 10.33, doubled: 5.79}
      - {horizon: "H60", baseline: 5.43, doubled: 3.29}
      - {horizon: "H90", baseline: 3.12, doubled: 2.55}
    x: horizon
    y: [baseline, doubled]
    names: ["Baseline (1.0x)", "Doubled (2.0x)"]
    colors: ["$primary", "$accent"]
    legend: {position: bottom, fontSize: 12}
    yAxis:
      title: "ROAS"
      gridLine: {color: "$grid"}
      min: 0
    xAxis:
      label: {fontSize: 12}
    dataLabels:
      show: true
      fontSize: 11
  - elementId: bottom-table
    elementType: table
    bounds: [60, 330, 1160, 200]
    columnWidths: [0.20, 0.20, 0.20, 0.20, 0.20]
    rowHeights: [0.25, 0.25, 0.25, 0.25]
    style: "$default"
    rows:
      - - content: {text: "Horizon"}
        - content: {text: "Baseline ROAS"}
        - content: {text: "2.0x ROAS"}
        - content: {text: "Absolute Decline"}
        - content: {text: "% Decline"}
      - - content: {text: "H30"}
        - content: {text: "10.33x"}
        - content: {text: "5.79x"}
        - content: {text: "-4.54x"}
        - content: {text: "-44%"}
      - - content: {text: "H60"}
        - content: {text: "5.43x"}
        - content: {text: "3.29x"}
        - content: {text: "-2.14x"}
        - content: {text: "-39%"}
      - - content: {text: "H90"}
        - content: {text: "3.12x"}
        - content: {text: "2.55x"}
        - content: {text: "-0.57x"}
        - content: {text: "-18%"}
  - elementId: bottom-insight
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 545, 1160, 140]
    content:
      fontSize: 16
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>Insight:</strong> Search shows the highest ROAS of any spend-enabled channel at H30, but faces the steepest diminishing returns. The 44% ROAS decline when doubling budget indicates Search campaigns are already operating near their optimal spend level. At only $463/day, Search is underfunded relative to its performance, but incremental dollars yield rapidly declining returns. The structural shift in Feb 2026 (test mean 4.1× training mean) further complicates the forecast.</p>
  - elementId: source
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 692, 1100, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Source: AIgnition Stage 5 Budget Simulation, Baseline 1.0x vs 2.0x Multiplier</p>
  - elementId: page-num
    elementType: text
    bounds: [1170, 692, 50, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [right, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>06</p>
